\lim\limits_{n\to\infty} C_n = \lim\limits_{n\to\infty} \dfrac{4n+3}{7n-5} = \dfrac{4}{7}
\epsilon > 0
N = \dfrac{41}{49\epsilon} + 1
n > \dfrac{41}{49\epsilon} + 1 \iff n-1 > \dfrac{41}{49\epsilon} \iff \epsilon(n-1) > \dfrac{41}{49} \iff \epsilon > \dfrac{41}{49n - 49} \iff
 \iff \epsilon > \dfrac{41}{49n-35} \iff \epsilon > \dfrac{28n+21-28n+20}{49n-35} \iff \dfrac{7(4n+3)-4(7n-5)}{7(7n-5)} \iff \epsilon > \dfrac{4n+3}{7n-5}-\dfrac{4}{7} \iff \epsilon >|\dfrac{4n+3}{7n-5}-\dfrac{4}{7}|
n \neq 0
\frac{4n+3}{7n-5} = \frac{4 + \frac{3}{n}}{7 - \frac{5}{n}}
 \lim_{n \to \infty}\frac{4n+3}{7n-5} = \lim_{n \to \infty}\frac{4 + \frac{3}{n}}{7 - \frac{5}{n}} = \frac{\lim\limits_{n \to \infty}(4+\frac{3}{n})}{\lim\limits_{n \to \infty}(7 - \frac{5}{n})} = \frac{4+0}{7+0} = \frac{4}{7}. 
lim_{n \to \infty} \frac{4n+3}{7n-5} = \frac{4}{7}
\frac{4n+3}{7n-5} - \frac{4}{7} =  \frac{7(4n+3)-4(7n-5)}{7(7n-5)} =  \frac{28n+21-28n+20}{49n-35} = \frac{41}{49n-35} 
